d="sdTag88" source="sdapi" category="assay" entity_type="None" role="None" text="binding" ext_ids="BAO_0002989" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="binding assay" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="https://bioportal.bioontology.org/ontologies/BAO/?p=classes&amp;conceptid=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bioassayontology.org%2Fbao%23">binding</sd-tag> <sd-tag id="sdTag89" source="sdapi" category="assay" entity_type="None" role="None" text="intensity" ext_ids="BAO_0000363" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="fluorescence intensity" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="https://bioportal.bioontology.org/ontologies/BAO/?p=classes&amp;conceptid=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bioassayontology.org%2Fbao%23">intensity</sd-tag>. n. s.: not significant. <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=105042"/></sd-panel><sd-panel panel_id="105043">The <sd-tag id="sdTag6" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="undefined" role="assayed" text="Mac2" ext_ids="" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="">Mac2</sd-tag> subdomain is crucial for <sd-tag id="sdTag94" source="sdapi" category="assay" entity_type="None" role="None" text="interacting" ext_ids="BAO_0002990" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="protein-protein interaction assay" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="https://bioportal.bioontology.org/ontologies/BAO/?p=classes&amp;conceptid=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bioassayontology.org%2Fbao%23">interacting</sd-tag> with <sd-tag id="sdTag7" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="gene" role="assayed" text="Paip1" ext_ids="10605" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="PAIP1" ext_tax_ids="9606" ext_tax_names="Homo sapiens" ext_urls="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gene/">Paip1</sd-tag>M. <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=105043"/></sd-panel><sd-panel panel_id="105044">Paip1M and SUD <sd-pretag id="sdPretag560116669sd" parent-tag-id="94">interaction</sd-pretag> was confirmed <em>in vitro</em> by a <sd-pretag id="sdPretag802383950sd" category="assay">gel</sd-pretag>-filtration assay. <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=105044"/></sd-panel></fig><fig id="39832"><title>.</title><label>Figure 2</label><graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?figure_id=39832"/><sd-panel panel_id="105049">Left <sd-pretag id="sdPretag777511279sd" category="assay">image</sd-pretag>: <sd-pretag id="sdPretag691317028sd" category="assay">crystal structure</sd-pretag> of the complex between <sd-pretag id="sdPretag854015213sd" parent-tag-id="6">Mac2</sd-pretag> (orange) and Paip1M (light blue). <sd-pretag id="sdPretag243875718sd" parent-tag-id="6">Mac2</sd-pretag> possesses a three-layer α/β/α fold. <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1325951185sd" type="geneprod" role="component">α1</sd-pretag>, 2, and 3, as well as η1 and α4, 5 form the two outside layers, whereas the β sheet (β3−β4-<sd-pretag id="sdPretag80650934sd" type="geneprod" role="component">β2</sd-pretag>−<sd-pretag id="sdPretag1624355385sd" type="geneprod" role="component">β5</sd-pretag>−<sd-pretag id="sdPretag532010365sd" type="geneprod" role="component">β6</sd-pretag>) forms the central layer. The first 16 residues of <sd-pretag id="sdPretag254178153sd" parent-tag-id="6">Mac2</sd-pretag> are shown in green. Paip1M comprises ten helices within two layers. <sd-pretag id="sdPretag292161538sd" type="geneprod" role="component">α1</sd-pretag>, 3, 5, 7, and 9 form one layer while <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1444298003sd" type="geneprod" role="component">α2</sd-pretag>, 4, 6, 8, and 10 form the other. The long loop region (Ile204−Thr212) is displayed in purple. The N and C termini of <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1182479287sd" parent-tag-id="6">Mac2</sd-pretag> and Paip1M (in <em>italics</em>) are marked. Right <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1996460840sd" category="assay">image</sd-pretag>: space-filling representation showing the tight <sd-pretag id="sdPretag298369423sd" parent-tag-id="94">interaction</sd-pretag> between <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1188495881sd" parent-tag-id="6">Mac2</sd-pretag> and Paip1M. <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=105049"/></sd-panel><sd-panel panel_id="105050">Left <sd-pretag id="sdPretag605256563sd" category="assay">image</sd-pretag>: F<sub>o</sub>-F<sub>c</sub> difference density omit map (2.5σ; blue) for the region Lys389−Thr408 of <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1864217866sd" parent-tag-id="6">Mac2</sd-pretag> (orange) in this complex. Right <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1275823497sd" category="assay">image</sd-pretag>: Conformational change of this region between free <sd-pretag id="sdPretag969407243sd" parent-tag-id="6">Mac2</sd-pretag> (blue; PDB entry: 2W2G, Tan <em>et al</em>, 2009) and <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1693643039sd" parent-tag-id="6">Mac2</sd-pretag> in this complex. <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=105050"/></sd-panel><sd-panel panel_id="105051">The <sd-pretag id="sdPretag213858276sd" category="assay">crystal structures</sd-pretag> of <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1955545478sd" parent-tag-id="6">Mac2</sd-pretag> (C; blue), Paip1M (D; red; PDB entry: 3RK6, Lei <em>et al</em>, 2011), and <sd-pretag id="sdPretag580104075sd" parent-tag-id="6">Mac2</sd-pretag>:Paip1M (E) fit the shape of <sd-pretag id="sdPretag2082157725sd" type="subcellular" role="component">envelopes</sd-pretag> derived from the small-angle X-ray scattering (SAXS) data. The blue and red dashed lines indicate the four (GSHM) and seventeen (GSHMASMTGGQQMGRGS) artificial residues remaining from the expression vectors in <sd-pretag id="sdPretag96952877sd" parent-tag-id="6">Mac2</sd-pretag> and Paip1M, resp. <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=105051"/></sd-panel></fig><fig id="39834"><title>.</title><label>Figure 3</label><graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?figure_id=39834"/><sd-panel panel_id="105052">The <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1181579240sd" parent-tag-id="6">Mac2</sd-pretag> and Paip1M <sd-pretag id="sdPretag889226217sd" parent-tag-id="94">interaction</sd-pretag> was impaired by removing the N-<sd-pretag id="sdPretag184884533sd" type="subcellular" role="component">terminal</sd-pretag> 16 residues as revealed by the <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1588718994sd" category="assay">gel</sd-pretag>-filtration assay. <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=105052"/></sd-panel><sd-panel panel_id="105053">I<strong>sothermal Titration Calorimetry (ITC) assay of <sd-pretag id="sdPretag387134988sd" parent-tag-id="6">Mac2</sd-pretag> <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1376628820sd" parent-tag-id="88">binding</sd-pretag> Paip1M. The <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1288721015sd" type="cell" role="component">raw</sd-pretag> calorimetric curve is displayed on top while the fitted <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1939889136sd" parent-tag-id="88">binding</sd-pretag> isotherm curve is at the bottom. The measured values are:</strong> N = 0.94 ± 0.01 (<sd-pretag id="sdPretag1172693847sd" parent-tag-id="88">binding</sd-pretag> stoichiometry); <em>K<sub>d</sub></em> = 15.5 ± 1.5 μM (<sd-pretag id="sdPretag460727937sd" category="assay">dissociation constant</sd-pretag>); ΔH = -6778 ± 149 cal/mol (standard molar enthalpy change for <sd-pretag id="sdPretag645964959sd" parent-tag-id="88">binding</sd-pretag>); ΔS = -0.716 cal/mol/K (standard molar entropy change). <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=105053"/></sd-panel><sd-panel panel_id="105054">Δ16-<sd-pretag id="sdPretag1785615071sd" parent-tag-id="6">Mac2</sd-pretag> lost <sd-pretag id="sdPretag969531010sd" type="cell" role="component">all</sd-pretag> <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1821651939sd" parent-tag-id="88">binding</sd-pretag> affinity to Paip1M in the ITC experiment. <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=105054"/></sd-panel><sd-panel panel_id="105055">ITC result of <sd-pretag id="sdPretag525758580sd" parent-tag-id="13">Mac1</sd-pretag>−<strong>2 <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1573273158sd" parent-tag-id="94">interacting</sd-pretag> with Paip1M. The experime